<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="368" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="3.[797,1393,1309,1737]" pageId="3" pageNumber="368">
Taxonomy of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Lesson" baseAuthorityYear="1826" box="[1011,1192,1427,1460]" class="Mammalia" family="Bathyergidae" genus="Bathyergus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="3" pageNumber="368" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hottentotus">C. hottentotus</taxonomicName>
has changed based on recent molecular phylogenetic and chromosomal studies. As a result, the formerly considered subspecies amatus and whyte: are now recognized as distinct species of Fukomys. Four subspecies are recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
